  "page": "Lemore/Theories",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table align=\"right\" width=\"180px\" style=\"float:right; margin: 0em 0em 1em 1em;\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<th style=\"text-align: center; background-color:#c2c2c2; font-size:12px; -moz-border-radius-topleft:10px;-moz-border-radius-topright:10px;\">&#160;Theories&#160;may&#160;be&#160;removed&#160;if&#160;...&#160;\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"font-size:11px; text-align: left; background-color:#eeeeee; font-weight:lighter;-moz-border-radius-bottomleft:10px;-moz-border-radius-bottomright:10px;padding-right: 1em; padding-left: .5em; padding-right: .5em;\">\n<ol><li>Stated as questions or possibilities.</li>\n<li>More appropriate for another article.</li>\n<li>Illogical or previously disproven.</li>\n<li>Proven by canon source, and moved to main page.</li>\n<li>Speculative and lacking any evidence to support arguments.</li>\n<li>Responding to another theory (use <a href=\"/index.php/Talk:Lemore/Theories\" title=\"Talk:Lemore/Theories\">discussion page</a> instead).</li></ol>\n<dl><dd><ul><li><small>This does not include responses that are also standalone theories.</small></li>\n<li><small>Usage of an indented bullet does not imply the statement is a response.</small></li></ul></dd></dl>\n</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><a href=\"/index.php/Lemore\" title=\"Lemore\">Lemore</a>'s identity is under debate, even in the text, where <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a> finds her extremely mysterious. She claims to be a <a href=\"/index.php/Septa\" title=\"Septa\">septa</a>, but shows little shame, and has stretchmarks on her belly that imply she has given birth.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Lemore even states that she is hiding her identity.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> Furthermore, Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Connington\" title=\"Jon Connington\">Jon Connington</a> occasionally thinks of her, and sometimes addresses her, as \"Lady Lemore\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> \n</p><p>Readers have ventured multiple theories about Lemore's true identity.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Mother_of_Tyene_Sand\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Mother of Tyene Sand</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Evidence_against\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Evidence against</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Mellario\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Mellario</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Evidence_against_2\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Evidence against</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Ashara_Dayne\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Ashara Dayne</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#Evidence_against_3\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Evidence against</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Mother_of_Tyene_Sand\">Mother of Tyene Sand</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lemore/Theories&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Mother of Tyene Sand\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Some readers believe Lemore is the mother of <a href=\"/index.php/Tyene_Sand\" title=\"Tyene Sand\">Tyene Sand</a>, a septa seduced by <a href=\"/index.php/Oberyn_Martell\" title=\"Oberyn Martell\">Oberyn Martell</a>. Lemore is a septa who has given birth before, as evidenced by the stretchmarks on her belly seen by <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a>. She is also roughly in her mid 40's, and Tyene is in her early 20's, which would lend further support to the theory.\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Evidence_against\">Evidence against</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lemore/Theories&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Evidence against\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Tyene Sand has golden hair. Oberyn Martell and Lemore both have dark hair, making it unlikely that their daughter would have light hair. It is possible that Lemore dyes her hair to further conceal her identity, but that seems unnecessarily cautious. Further, if Lemore were Tyene's mother, it would be strange for her not to have communicated with her daughter or anyone else back in Dorne to give support to  <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_Targaryen_(Young_Griff)\" title=\"Aegon Targaryen (Young Griff)\">Aegon Targaryen</a>'s legitimacy.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Mellario\">Mellario</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lemore/Theories&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Mellario\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Another possibility is that Lemore is actually Lady <a href=\"/index.php/Mellario\" title=\"Mellario\">Mellario</a>, the estranged <a href=\"/index.php/Norvoshi\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Norvoshi\">Norvoshi</a> wife of <a href=\"/index.php/Doran_Martell\" title=\"Doran Martell\">Doran Martell</a>. Lady Lemore has brown hair (and possibly brown eyes), like <a href=\"/index.php/Quentyn_Martell\" title=\"Quentyn Martell\">Quentyn Martell</a>, and she is a handsome woman with an outgoing and sexually uninhibited personality, like <a href=\"/index.php/Arianne_Martell\" title=\"Arianne Martell\">Arianne Martell</a>.\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Evidence_against_2\">Evidence against</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lemore/Theories&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Evidence against\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>It would be unusual for a woman from Norvos to pose as a septa, or to have extensive knowledge of the <a href=\"/index.php/Faith_of_the_Seven\" title=\"Faith of the Seven\">Faith of the Seven</a>. Furthermore, Tyrion doesn't notice any accent in Lemore's <a href=\"/index.php/Common_Tongue\" title=\"Common Tongue\">Common Tongue</a>, which would also be unusual for a person born in <a href=\"/index.php/Essos\" title=\"Essos\">Essos</a>. And again, it would be strange for her not to have communicated with Doran or anyone else in Dorne to give support to Aegon's legitimacy; however, this could be explain by Mellario having taken a vow of secrecy, or her goal being actually to take revenge on her estranged husband, by carrying out before him the plan to place a Targaryen on the <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Throne\" title=\"Iron Throne\">Iron Throne</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Ashara_Dayne\">Ashara Dayne</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lemore/Theories&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Ashara Dayne\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Another speculation is that Lemore is actually <a href=\"/index.php/Ashara_Dayne\" title=\"Ashara Dayne\">Ashara Dayne</a>, former companion to Princess <a href=\"/index.php/Elia_Martell\" title=\"Elia Martell\">Elia Martell</a>. It is theorized that Ashara did not in fact commit suicide after delivering a stillborn daughter and receiving her <a href=\"/index.php/Arthur_Dayne\" title=\"Arthur Dayne\">dead brother</a>'s <a href=\"/index.php/Dawn\" title=\"Dawn\">sword</a> from <a href=\"/index.php/Eddard_Stark\" title=\"Eddard Stark\">Eddard Stark</a>, but went to aid Elia's son Aegon in Essos.\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Evidence_against_3\">Evidence against</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lemore/Theories&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Evidence against\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>When observing Lemore on the <i><a href=\"/index.php/Shy_Maid\" title=\"Shy Maid\">Shy Maid</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a> never makes note of her eye colour, which, if she were Ashara, would be very notable, as Ashara's eyes were described as being a \"haunting <a href=\"/index.php/Purple_eyes\" title=\"Purple eyes\">violet</a>\" colour. And again, it is strange that Ashara did not contact the Martells to assert Aegon's legitimacy, or reveal herself when Jon Connington sent a letter to beg for their aid.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lemore/Theories&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Radwd14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons-Chapter_14\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons-Chapter 14\">Chapter 14</a>, Tyrion IV.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Radwd22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons-Chapter_22\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons-Chapter 22\">Chapter 22</a>, Tyrion VI.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Radwd24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons-Chapter_24\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons-Chapter 24\">Chapter 24</a>, The Lost Lord.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260403143210\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.019 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.020 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 336/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 8654/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 2106/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 66/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 8/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 1445/5000000 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%   11.860      1 -total\n 74.41%    8.825      3 Template:Ref\n 49.27%    5.843      3 Template:Ref/core\n 15.99%    1.897      1 Template:References\n  6.81%    0.808      1 Template:Theory_Policy\n-->\n</div>\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key westeros_awoiaftest-mw_:pcache:idhash:12828-0!canonical and timestamp 20260403143210 and revision id 328004\n -->\n",
